1 in 44 children in this country are affected by autism, yet they continue to be amongst the most underserved populations in our community. Please join me in supporting Autism Charlotte’s effort to launch Mecklenburg County’s first ever Academy for Students with Autism. Programs are focused on addressing the educational, social, and developmental needs of children on the autism spectrum in a place and environment they can call home.

Learn more about Autism Charlotte’s A Place to Call Home Campaign at www.autismcharlotte.org in the bio!

Autism has personally impacted my family and has been my cause since entering the league. On March 31st, I’m partnering with Autism Charlotte to host a gala at BOA Stadium in support of Charlotte’s first ever Academy for Students with Autism. It’s going to be a fun night with great music, food, drinks, and auctions. I would love the support of my family, friends, and fans. Tickets are selling fast, click the link in my bio to secure yours.

@the_racing_warehouse 🤝🏽 @nfl 

Ian Thomas from The Carolina Panthers needed a display for this beautiful @austindillon3 Drivers Suit. 

This suit will be on auction March 31st, at BOA Stadium in support of Charlotte's first ever Academy for Students with Autism.🫶🏼

Happy to support such a great cause 👍🏼🧩

In April we celebrated National Autism Awareness and hosted a gala to fundraise for Autism Charlotte in support of their new academy for students with autism. This year’s event was tremendously successful and netted the most we’ve raised in AC’s history. You were a part of making that happen, and I want thank each of you for helping to shine a light on this important cause with both your presence and your giving. We could not have done it without your help, and I hope that you will take a moment to visit AC during their May 12th Open House and get a first hand view of what your support has helped to accomplish.

Praising Him through every season of life

Year 6 🔋
